    "description": "<ul><li><p><span>At any moment, if you have a full set of active Soul Beads, you may imbue one weapon with them. Until this spell ends, the weapon gains a +3 bonus to Accuracy Checks, and its damage ignores Resistances.</span></p></li><li><p><span>If it’s a melee weapon, it also gains the ranged property, and its attacks can now be launched from afar.</span></p></li><li><p><span>If you have that weapon equipped while casting this spell, you may perform a free attack with it as part of the same action.</span></p></li><li><p><span>You lose access to beads used, and they don’t count toward the Clarity Skill while imbued in your weapon.</span></p></li><li><p><span>You can generate Soul Beads as normal on the next turn.</span></p></li><li><p><span>The same weapon cannot benefit from this skill twice.</span></p></li></ul>",
